<inglise>In this Procedure, the following definitions are used: </inglise>
<eesti>Lennuliiklustasu - lennuliikluteenuste eest v&otilde;etava tasu (marsruudi navigatsioonitasu, terminali navigatsioonitasu, maandumistasu, parkimistasu, reisijatasu ja starditasu) &uuml;ldnimetus. </eesti>
<inglise>"Air traffic charges" mean charges levied on air traffic services (route charge, terminal charge, landing charge, parking charge, passenger charge and take-off charge). </inglise>
<eesti>Marsruudi navigatsioonitasu - lennujuhtimisteenuse eest v&otilde;etav tasu Eesti lennuinfopiirkonnas, kui &otilde;hus&otilde;iduk lendab instrumentaallennureeglite j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>"Route charge" means the charge levied on air traffic control services within the Estonian flight information region if the aircraft flies according to the instrument flight rules. </inglise>
<eesti>Terminali navigatsioonitasu - tasu, mis v&otilde;etakse lennujuhtimisteenuse ja lennuv&auml;lja lennuinfoteenuse eest, kui &otilde;hus&otilde;iduk lendab antud lennuv&auml;lja l&auml;hilennujuhtimisalas, selle lennuv&auml;lja lennuinfotsoonis ja maandub sellel lennuv&auml;ljal. </eesti>
<inglise>"Terminal charge" means the charge levied on air traffic control services and on flight information services of an airport if the aircraft flies in the control zone and aerodrome flight information zone of such airport and lands at the airport. </inglise>
<eesti>Baseeruv &otilde;hus&otilde;iduk - &otilde;hus&otilde;iduk, mille omanik v&otilde;i k&auml;itaja on s&otilde;lminud selle lennuv&auml;ljaga lepingu &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki alaliseks baseerumiseks sellel lennuv&auml;ljal. </eesti>
<inglise>"Stationing aircraft" means an aircraft the owner or operator of which has entered into a contract with an airport for the permanent stationing of the aircraft at the airport. </inglise>
<eesti>Lennuv&auml;ljatasu - lennuv&auml;ljateenuste eest v&otilde;etava tasu (maandumis-, parkimis-, reisija- ja starditasu) &uuml;ldnimetus. </eesti>
<inglise>"Airport charges" mean charges levied on airport services (landing, parking, passenger and take-off charges). </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik &otilde;hus&otilde;iduk - &otilde;hus&otilde;iduk, mida kasutatakse kaitsev&auml;e-, tolli- v&otilde;i politseiteenistuses. </eesti>
<inglise>"State aircraft" means an aircraft which is used in armed forces, customs or police services. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsimis-p&auml;&auml;stelend - Merevalvekeskuse, lennup&auml;&auml;ste koordinatsioonikeskuse v&otilde;i v&auml;lisriigi vastava teenistusega koosk&otilde;lastatud lend otsimis- ja p&auml;&auml;stet&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>"Search and rescue flight" means a flight for performing search or rescue work, concorded with the Maritime Rescue Co-ordination Centre, Aeronautical Rescue Co-ordination Centre or a corresponding service of a foreign state. </inglise>
<eesti>Siseriiklik liiklus - lennud, mille l&auml;hte- ja sihtlennuv&auml;li on Eestis. </eesti>
<inglise>"Domestic traffic" means flights the airport of departure and destination of which is in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>Konveiermaandumine - stardi- ja maandumisharjutus, kus lennuk alustab starti enne l&auml;bijooksu l&otilde;ppu. </eesti>
<inglise>"Touch-and-go landing" means an exercise of take-off and landing where the aircraft commences a new take-off before coming to a complete stop. </inglise>
<eesti>Madall&auml;henemine - &otilde;hus&otilde;iduki instrumentaal- v&otilde;i visuaall&auml;henemise harjutus, kus &otilde;hus&otilde;iduk alustab uut l&auml;henemist v&otilde;i j&auml;tkab lendu p&auml;rast vajalike lennuparameetrite saavutamist lennurajale l&auml;henemisel. </eesti>
<inglise>"Approach for training purposes" means an instrument approach or visual approach exercise of an aircraft where the aircraft commences a new approach or continues flying after the required flight characteristics have been achieved upon approaching the runway. </inglise>
<eesti>Ortodroomne teekond - k&otilde;ige l&uuml;hem teekond kahe punkti vahel m&ouml;&ouml;da suurringjoont. </eesti>
<inglise>"Great circle distance" means the route which follows the shortest arc of a great circle between two points. </inglise>
